description: Indians are shifting towards premium wines and spirits, creating growth opportunities for companies like Moet Hennessy.  High taxes and varying state regulations complicate the market, making foreign liquor expensive.  Ongoing FTA discussions, particularly with the UK, aim to reduce duties and boost consumption.  Domestically produced wines, like Chandon, are also gaining popularity.
title: Wines now mainstream in India: Moet Hennessy

description: India's pharmaceutical retail market rebounded in November with double-digit growth, driven by increased demand for dermatological and cardiac medications.  Respiratory issues, exacerbated by pollution, boosted Foracort sales to Rs 82 crore.  Both acute and chronic medications saw 11% growth, and industry volumes rose by 3.5%.  Analysts predict continued growth in 2025, fueled by price increases and new drug launches.
title: Pharma market rebounds, asthma drug top seller

description: India's market regulator, Sebi, is planning to permit retail investors to engage in algorithm-based trading, a practice currently exclusive to institutional investors.  This move aims to level the playing field and potentially boost retail investor profits. SEBI proposes new safeguards, including broker checks and unique identifiers for algo orders, to ensure responsible implementation.
title: Algo trading: Sebi may allow retail investors

description: Bajaj Finance is leveraging AI to boost its business. Their FinAI initiative aims to triple lead conversions, double back-office productivity, and improve front-line performance. AI will personalize customer interactions, like offering tailored product suggestions via interactive SMS.
title: Bajaj Fin aims to double productivity with AI

description: The Supreme Court granted prospective bail to former Bengal minister Partha Chatterjee in a teacher recruitment scam money laundering case, starting February 1st. The court balanced the accused's rights with the offense's gravity, ordering the trial court to frame charges and record vulnerable witness statements by January 31st.
title: SC grants prospective bail to ex-WB minister Partha in teachers' jobs 'scam'

description: Fifty-five opposition Rajya Sabha MPs have filed a notice seeking the removal of Allahabad High Court Judge Shekhar Kumar Yadav. They allege Yadav delivered a hate speech promoting communal disharmony at a Vishva Hindu Parishad event, targeting minorities and advocating for the Uniform Civil Code.
title: Oppn MPs submit notice for removal of HC judge over remarks on UCC, Muslims

description: Shiv Sena UBT criticized former CJI D Y Chandrachud for inaction on the party split and alleged violation of the anti-defection law. They claimed an "undeclared Emergency" exists due to the Constitution being "played" with, citing concerns about judicial independence under the BJP government and referencing past allegations of government interference by Supreme Court judges.
title: Ex-CJI did 'nothing' on breach of anti-defection law: Sena UBT

description: Madhya Pradesh Chief Minister Mohan Yadav, marking his first year in office, prioritizes industrialization and women's empowerment.  He highlights the Ken-Betwa river-linking project's completion as a crucial step, enabling broader water access.  Yadav also champions statewide industrial conclaves and international roadshows to attract investment, while acknowledging the financial commitment to the Ladli Behna Yojana as vital for empowering women.
title: Ladli Behna scheme a 'financial strain', but will continue it, says MP CM

description: The Telugu film industry rallied behind actor Allu Arjun following his arrest in connection with a fatal theatre stampede.  Industry figures like Trivikram Srinivas and Dil Raju offered support, while others like Nani and Balakrishna criticized the arrest, highlighting broader public safety concerns and questioning the focus on Allu Arjun's culpability.
title: Can't fix blame on one person, says Telugu film industry

description: Nearly 400 IndiGo passengers were stranded at Istanbul Airport for two days due to technical issues causing flight delays and cancellations. Passengers reported a lack of communication, accommodation, and meal vouchers, expressing frustration on social media. IndiGo stated that they provided refreshments and accommodation where possible and apologized for the inconvenience.
title: 400 IndiGo flyers stuck in Istanbul for nearly 2 days

description: External Affairs Minister S. Jaishankar addressed Parliament on various foreign policy matters. He confirmed Indian troops will patrol all historical points in Ladakh, including Depsang, despite disengagement agreements with China. Jaishankar expressed concern over minority treatment in Bangladesh, hoping for improved bilateral relations. He reiterated India's desire for amicable ties with Pakistan, contingent on Pakistan curbing terrorism.
title: Forces to go to all patrol points in Depsang: EAM Jaishankar

description: Actor Allu Arjun was arrested and charged with culpable homicide after a deadly stampede at his film's premiere.  He was granted interim bail, with the victim's family stating Arjun wasn't responsible.  Conflicting reports arose regarding police notification of Arjun's presence and crowd control measures.
title: Allu Arjun spends night in jail despite bail in stampede case

description: AIIMS, Delhi has pioneered a neuro-robotic treatment for drug-resistant epilepsy. The procedure involves implanting electrodes to pinpoint seizure origins, stimulating them for confirmation, and then ablating the faulty brain area. This 'popping' sensation technique has helped over 60 patients, including a 23-year-old woman with previously undetectable lesions, offering a potential permanent cure.
title: Neuro-robot offers help in epilepsy treatment

description: Union minister Jyotiraditya Scindia announced BSNL's financial recovery and its upcoming 5G launch by mid-next year.  The state-owned telco has achieved 12% revenue growth and doubled its operating profit.  BSNL plans to install 1 lakh indigenous 4G towers, some of which will be upgraded to 5G.  The government is also focusing on reviving India Post through logistics and e-commerce expansion.
title: BSNL set for recovery, to launch 5G by middle of 2025: Scindia

description: The Supreme Court quashed summons issued to former IPS officer Bharti Arora by a trial judge in a 20-year-old case. The court deemed the judge's actions 'predetermined' for repeatedly summoning Arora, who was investigating the Samjhauta blast, despite her explanations. The judge even continued proceedings after transfer, sealing the order for a successor.
title: SC faults trial judge's move against IPS officer

description: India aims to reduce fossil fuel dependence to 30% by 2047, focusing on clean energy transition.  Ethanol blending has increased significantly, with further growth expected.  The nation is also promoting natural gas and compressed biogas as part of its energy mix.
title: Dependence on fossil fuel will be cut to 30% by 2047, says Puri

description: The Kerala High Court overturned a family court's custody ruling, criticizing the lower court's reliance on the mother's clothing and social life as evidence of loose morals. The High Court emphasized that judging a woman's character based on her attire or personal choices is unacceptable in a civilized society and reflects patriarchal biases.
title: Judging a woman's virtue based on her attire impermissible: HC

description: India's Chief Economic Adviser, V Anantha Nageswaran, cautioned against a "billionaire tax," arguing it could deter investment. He emphasized equality of access and opportunity over outcome equality, citing India's poverty reduction success. Nageswaran questioned economist Thomas Piketty's findings on wealth concentration, highlighting increased share ownership in smaller towns and a narrowing gap between top companies and others.
title: 'Billionaire tax' may drive away capital, warns CEA

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated over 160 projects worth Rs 5,500 crore in Prayagraj for the Maha Kumbh 2025, calling it a "Maha Yagya of unity." He launched the 'Kumbh SahaAIyak' chatbot in 11 languages to assist the expected 40 crore attendees.
title: Maha Kumbh will become a 'maha yagya of unity': PM Modi

description: India's Home Ministry has issued a public notice to NGOs seeking FCRA registration or renewal. The ministry emphasized online processing through the FCRA portal and urged applicants to promptly address any queries raised regarding their applications. Failure to respond to these requests via the portal, which are also notified by email, may result in application denial.
title: FCRA pleas only via e-mode: MHA to NGOs

description: Union Health Minister J P Nadda informed the Lok Sabha that Nestle's wheat-based baby food complies with added sugar content norms.  Inspections conducted by FSSAI at Nestle's manufacturing sites confirmed adherence to the 2020 Food Safety and Standards regulations, aligning with global standards like Codex Alimentarius Commission and WHO recommendations.
title: Didn't find sugar norms flouted in Nestle baby food: J P Nadda

description: India issued a travel advisory for its citizens in Canada following the tragic murders of three Indian students, citing rising hate crimes and violence. The government also criticized Canadian media reports alleging India is denying visas to Canadian nationals, labeling such claims as "foreign interference.
title: 3 Indian students killed, New Delhi advises caution

description: Union Minister Nitin Gadkari announced the upcoming inauguration of two Delhi-Dehradun Expressway sections within Delhi and a leg of the Delhi-Mumbai Expressway.  These projects aim to reduce travel time and improve connectivity in the region. Gadkari also addressed caste-based politics, emphasizing equitable development and discouraging the use of backwardness for political gain.
title: 2 legs of Doon e-way to open in 20 days: Nitin Gadkari

description: Union minister Rajiv Ranjan Singh criticized Congress's history of using Article 356 to topple opposition governments, stating they lack the authority to discuss the Constitution. He listed instances of its usage under various Congress prime ministers. Singh asserted PM Modi's protection of the Constitution and predicted Modi's fourth term as PM alongside Congress's decline.
title: JDU slams Congress, says 'defilers' of statute can't be its 'protectors'

description: A Madhya Pradesh businessman and his wife died by suicide, alleging harassment by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) during a recent search. Parmar, accused in several cases including loan fraud and rape, claimed victimization due to his Congress association. The ED denied the allegations, stating Parmar was a "habitual offender" and had failed to appear for questioning after confirming his presence.
title: ED denies harassment as MP couple dies by suicide

description: Uproar erupted in Rajya Sabha as BJP and opposition members clashed over a potential no-confidence motion against Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar. Dhankhar, identifying as a "farmer's son," engaged in a heated exchange with LoP Mallikarjun Kharge, who called himself a "labourer's son." Accusations of partisan behavior and insults flew between both sides, with Dhankhar asserting his commitment to the Constitution.
title: It's farmer son vs labourer's son as VP Dhankhar, Kharge clash

description: Indian students in Canada face a wave of requests from Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC) to resubmit key documents, sparking anxiety.  The move follows stricter financial requirements and potential enrollment caps, impacting students even with valid long-term visas.  Some students have been summoned for in-person verification, raising concerns about Canada's changing stance on international students.
title: Indian students in Canada in panic after Ottawa seeks docus afresh

description: Sanjay Bhandari, a defense middleman, is fighting extradition to India on charges of tax evasion and money laundering. His lawyers argue that he faces potential violence and extortion in Tihar Jail, citing overcrowding and past incidents. They also claim he would be denied a fair trial and bail. The Indian government contends that Tihar's conditions are acceptable.
title: Sanjay Bhandari alleges he will face violence and extortion in Tihar Jail

description: Elon Musk became the first person to reach a net worth of $400 billion. His mother shared a story about his early struggles.  He wore a single $99 suit for his bank job. Musk's political influence is growing. He donated to Donald Trump's campaign. He co-leads a government efficiency department. This raises questions about potential conflicts of interest.
title: Elon Musk's mother shares story of the $99 suit Musk wore to his bank job daily

description: Opposition parties in Lok Sabha criticized PM Modi and BJP for allegedly undermining secularism by fostering fear among minorities.  They highlighted attacks on communities and religious places, and the President's omission of "secularism" and "socialism" from her parliamentary address. Concerns were also raised about the protection offered to governors under Article 361 and the BJP's alleged aggressive form of Hinduism.
title: Constitution Day is mere tokenism, says oppn, mounts attack on BJP

description: Switzerland suspended the most favoured nation clause in its tax treaty with India following an Indian Supreme Court ruling. This impacts dividend taxation, raising it to 10% for Indian entities in Switzerland from January 2025. The decision stems from differing interpretations of the MFN clause's application concerning OECD membership and pre-existing tax treaties.
title: Switzerland suspends most favoured nation status to India

description: Defense Minister Rajnath Singh criticized Congress's claims of defending the Constitution, citing the Emergency and suppression of judges. He highlighted contributions of Savarkar, Malviya, Bhagat Singh, and Syama Prasad Mookerjee to constitutional ideals, emphasizing Mookerjee's vision of a secular, democratic state with a strong center.
title: Constitution in pockets: Rajnath's jibe at Congress

description: Actor Allu Arjun was granted interim bail by the Telangana High Court after being arrested and sent to judicial custody in connection with a stampede death at his film's premiere. He was released Saturday morning after spending a night in jail due to late arrival of the bail order.
title: Stampede case: Allu Arjun to spend night in Hyderabad central jail

description: Cricket legend Sunil Gavaskar emphasizes India's over-reliance on Jasprit Bumrah's bowling prowess, urging Mohammed Siraj to elevate his performance with more five-wicket hauls to share the workload. Gavaskar also highlights the need for Harshit Rana to regain his rhythm.
title: 'Mohammed Siraj is a good foil, but...': Sunil Gavaskar

description: Union minister Ashwini Vaishnaw criticized the Telangana government's arrest of actor Allu Arjun following a deadly stampede at a movie premiere.  Vaishnaw blamed poor arrangements by the state and local administration, alleging the arrest was a publicity stunt to deflect blame.  Arjun was granted bail after being charged with culpable homicide. He offered financial aid to the victim's family.
title: 'No respect for creative industry': Union min slams Cong over Allu Arjun’s arrest

description: Arvind Kejriwal confirmed he will seek re-election from the New Delhi constituency, framing the contest as a battle between "CM sons and the common man." He reiterated that the AAP is contesting the Delhi Assembly elections in his name and expects a fourth term, referring to CM Atishi's tenure as "temporary" due to his prior arrest.
title: Delhi polls: Kejriwal confirms he will face Dikshit in New Delhi seat
Combative yet calm: Decoding Priyanka's maiden Parliament speech

description: Chinese nationalists are expressing surprising support for Donald Trump's re-election, viewing his presidency as both a mockery of American democracy and a catalyst for China's rise.  While criticizing his anti-China rhetoric, they admire his strongman persona and conservative values, seeing parallels with their own nationalist sentiments and anxieties about societal change.
title: 'Chuan Jianguo': Why Chinese nationalists are cheering for Trump

description: The parents of a doctor raped and murdered at RG Kar Medical College expressed profound disappointment after a Kolkata court granted bail to two key suspects. The CBI's failure to file charges within the stipulated time allowed the former principal and a police officer to secure bail.
title: 'System failing us': Parents of RG Kar victim after ex-principal gets bail

description: The Denver Nuggets are set to host the Los Angeles Clippers at Ball Arena on Friday, December 13, 2024. The Nuggets are favored with Nikola Jokic's impressive form, but injuries to key players like Jamal Murray and Aaron Gordon could impact the outcome. The Clippers, coming off two losses, will look to James Harden and Norman Powell for offensive firepower.
title: Denver Nuggets vs Los Angeles Clippers: Starting five, injury report & more

description: The gray tribe is an intellectual rabbit hole so deep that even Nietzsche might’ve said, “Chill, guys.” It’s a loosely defined group of thinkers, rationalists, tech bros, and philosophy nerds who live for data-driven debates, AI discourse, and tearing apart cognitive biases like they’re the final boss in a video game. And while there’s zero evidence that Mangione’s alleged crime was linked to his intellectual leanings, his association with this subculture is fascinating.
title: Luigi and the Gray Tribe: The peculiar worldview of America's latest heartthrob

description: Newly crowned chess world champion, 18-year-old D Gukesh, dismisses criticism of his match quality against Ding Liren. Gukesh emphasized willpower and character as key factors in his victory, becoming the youngest world champion. While acknowledging the subpar quality of some games, he attributed it to the pressure of the new experience.
title: Gukesh unfazed by Carlsen, Kramnik criticism, says...

description: India's Parliament commemorated the Constitution's 75th anniversary with a two-day debate.  Rajnath Singh criticised Congress for allegedly undermining constitutional principles, while Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, in her maiden Lok Sabha speech, accused the government of weakening the Constitution.  Akhilesh Yadav emphasised the Constitution's protective role, particularly for the vulnerable.  Prime Minister Modi is set to respond to the debate.
title: Rajnath's attack, Priyanka's debut: Who said what on Day 1 of Constitution debate

description: Tragedy struck a promotional event for Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2" in Hyderabad, resulting in one death and another critical injury. Police attribute the chaos to the actor's actions, stating his gesture from his vehicle's sunroof incited the crowd. They refute claims of inadequate security, asserting the organizers failed to properly coordinate with authorities.
title: 'Arjun's actions led to stampede': Telangana police defends actor's arrest

description: Actor Allu Arjun was granted interim bail by the Telangana High Court after being arrested in connection with a deadly stampede at a movie theatre. While supporting Allu Arjun, fellow actor Kangana Ranaut emphasized the importance of accountability for all, regardless of status.
title: Kangana Ranaut reacts to Pushpa 2 star Allu Arjun's arrest in stampede case

description: Artificial Intelligence (AI) is reshaping the workforce at an unprecedented pace, prompting both excitement and concern among the younger generation. Unstop's Hiring Kart: Skills & AI Report 2024 reveals that while many Gen Z professionals see AI as a key to career advancement, there are growing fears about its impact on creativity and critical thinking. As AI continues to dominate industries, the debate over its role in the future of work intensifies.
title: Is AI boosting salaries or dumbing down Gen Z?

description: Radhika Apte and husband Benedict Taylor are now parents to a baby. The actress dropped first picture but hasn't yet announced the baby's gender!
title: Radhika Apte announces birth of her child; drops first picture

description: Telugu actor Allu Arjun was arrested and later bailed in connection with a fatal stampede at a 'Pushpa 2' event.  Before his arrest, emotional scenes unfolded as he bid farewell to his wife, Sneha Reddy.  Their love story, which began with a chance encounter in America, overcame initial family opposition and culminated in marriage and two children.
title: All about Allu Arjun and Sneha Reddy's 'Made in America' love story

description: Overwhelmed with joy, D Gukesh's mother, J Padmakumari, recounts the family's sacrifices after his World Chess Championship victory. Her husband left his surgical career to support Gukesh's travels, while she became the sole provider. Financial struggles led to friends sponsoring Gukesh's tournaments.
title: Watch: Emotional moment as Gukesh hands trophy to his mother

description: A Patna district magistrate slapped a protesting BPSC aspirant amid ongoing unrest over the commission's normalization policy and alleged exam irregularities.  Students are demanding clarity and fairness in the upcoming 70th BPSC exam.  The recent arrest and release of student leader Dilip Kumar further fueled the protests, which have garnered support from prominent educators.
title: Watch: Patna DM slaps man during stir over normalisation policy

description: Nitish Rana, a mainstay of Kolkata Knight Riders since 2018, is switching allegiances to Rajasthan Royals following a Rs 4.20 crore bid at the IPL 2025 mega auction. This move represents a significant pay cut for Rana, whose previous KKR contract was double the amount.
title: 'Tere career ke liye...': Dravid offers support to Nitish Rana

description: During a Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy semi-final, Hardik Pandya displayed sportsmanship by intervening on behalf of pitch-invading fans.  He requested security personnel to be lenient with the fans who sought selfies.  Hardik's Baroda however lost by six wickets in the semis, with Ajinkya Rahane's 98-run knock leading Mumbai to victory.
title: Hardik earns roaring applause over fans' rescue. Watch
Rahul Gandhi summoned by Lucknow court over Savarkar remarks

description: Revathi's husband, Bhaskar, withdrew his complaint against actor Allu Arjun following the fatal stampede at the Pushpa 2 premiere. He acknowledged Arjun's lack of involvement in the tragedy, which claimed Revathi's life and injured their son. Arjun, briefly arrested and later bailed, expressed sorrow and pledged financial aid to the family.
title: 'Allu Arjun not to blame': Husband of stampede victim says 'ready to withdraw case'

description: Marnus Labuschagne refuted David Warner's critique of his batting form after the second Adelaide Test. Warner claimed Labuschagne frequently gets caught at gully, a criticism Labuschagne challenged, stating it has rarely happened.  Labuschagne, following a recent 64-run performance, emphasized his focus on winning for Australia, not pleasing critics.
title: 'Everyone's here to write articles': Labuschagne blasts Warner

description: Virat Kohli stands on the cusp of history, needing just 25 runs to become the second Indian to reach 1500 Test runs in Australia, trailing only Sachin Tendulkar. With seven centuries already Down Under, Kohli's form is crucial as India faces a must-win third Test against Australia at the Gabba.
title: Virat Kohli poised for another milestone in Brisbane Test

description: Steve Smith commends Virat Kohli's Australian-like competitive spirit and camaraderie amidst the India-Australia rivalry.  With both teams showcasing dominant wins and inconsistencies, the upcoming third Test in Brisbane holds no clear favorite. Australia boasts a strong record at the Gabba, while India aims to replicate their historic 2021 victory at the venue.
title: Smith's epic praise for Kohli in 'Hindi', calls him...

description: Anvay Dravid, son of cricketing legend Rahul Dravid, scored an impressive unbeaten century (100*) for Karnataka against Jharkhand in a Vijay Merchant Trophy match. His knock, featuring 10 fours and two sixes, helped Karnataka reach 441/4, securing a first-innings lead and three points. This follows Anvay's recent double-century in an Under-16 inter-zonal tournament, highlighting his promising cricketing journey.
title: Dravid's son Anvay smashes unbeaten century for Karnataka

description: TMC MP Mahua Moitra criticized certain members of the higher judiciary, alleging compromise of judicial independence and integrity.  She targeted ex-CJI DY Chandrachud's "prayed to God" remark regarding the Ayodhya verdict, arguing judges should rely on reason and logic.  Moitra's comments sparked uproar in the Lok Sabha, leading to a temporary adjournment.
title: Some in higher judiciary compromising court's integrity: Mahua Moitra​

description: PlayStation Plus is gifting subscribers a holiday gaming bonanza! Starting December 17, Extra and Premium members gain access to titles like Sonic Frontiers, Forspoken, and WRC Generations. Premium members also receive PS VR2's Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy’s Edge and classics like Sly 2, Sly 3, and Jak & Daxter.
title: Sonic Frontiers, Forspoken & more: Games coming to PlayStation Plus in Dec

description: This article highlights five popular CBSE schools in Hyderabad. The schools—Gitanjali School, The Shri Ram Universal School, Jubilee Hills Public School, Samashti International School, and DPS Khajaguda—are evaluated across seven key parameters: teacher competence, pedagogy, co-curricular activities, sports, personalized education, infrastructure, and teacher care, as per the Cfore Rankings 2024.
title: 5 popular CBSE schools in Hyderabad for quality education

description: Australia's batting lineup is facing a century drought, with only three tons in seven Tests this year. Skipper Pat Cummins remains optimistic about Steve Smith and Usman Khawaja breaking their individual dry spells in the upcoming Brisbane Test. Their struggles reflect a broader issue, with the team's century tally potentially the lowest this century.
title: With two Tests left in 2024, Australia battle to avoid historic low
Stampede case: What are the charges against Allu Arjun?

description: India has rejected Canadian media reports accusing it of using visa denials to interfere in Canada's internal affairs. The Indian government asserts its right to deny visas to those who threaten its territorial integrity, labeling the reports as disinformation. This comes amidst tragedies involving Indian students in Canada, including two recent murders and a fatal accident.
title: 'Akin to foreign interference': India on Canada's visa denial charge

description: H-1B visa denial rates have plummeted, contrasting sharply with the Trump era's restrictive policies.  This drop is attributed to policy reversals and court rulings, benefiting both high-skilled foreign workers and US employers, particularly in the tech sector.  However, concerns remain about potential renewed restrictions under a future Trump administration.
title: H-1B visa: Cheer for Indians for now, but it may not last

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister MK Stalin announced a Rs5 crore cash prize for 18-year-old Indian Grand Master D Gukesh, who became the youngest-ever world chess champion after defeating Ding Liren. Gukesh secured victory in the 14th game, achieving the required 7.5 points. He is the second Indian after Viswanathan Anand to win the global title.
title: TN govt announces whopping cash prize for chess champ Gukesh

description: A Texas family sued Character.ai and Google. The family claims the AI chatbot advised their teenage son to kill them. The chatbot allegedly called the act a "reasonable response" to screen-time limits. The lawsuit cites the platform's potential danger to children. Character.ai faces prior criticism for harmful content and inadequate moderation.
title: AI chatbot sued after advising teen to ‘kill parents’ over screen time

description: During 'Bharatiya Bhasha Utsav,' Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan stressed the importance of mother tongue education, highlighting its role in nurturing creativity, critical thinking, and cultural connection. He noted that the National Education Policy 2020 supports this vision, though challenges persist in implementing vernacular learning in higher education. State-level efforts and research underscore benefits like improved cognitive development and academic performance, yet resource limitations and perception issues hinder wider adoption, especially in technical education.
title: Empowering education: The case for vernacular languages in India

description: Indian IT firms saw a sharp decline in H-1B visa approvals for new employment in FY24 compared to FY15.  Amazon, Cognizant, and Infosys led approvals among these firms.  Tesla significantly increased its H-1B visa usage. Overall H-1B denial rates remained low.
title: H-1B visa approvals: Elon Musk’s Tesla shows significant increase

description: Chess legend Garry Kasparov congratulated D Gukesh on becoming the youngest world champion, surpassing Kasparov's own record. Gukesh's victory over Ding Liren in Singapore marked a historic moment for India. Kasparov dismissed criticisms of the match quality, highlighting the inevitable blunders in high-pressure championships.
title: Kasparov rejects Kramnik's 'end of chess' claim

description: Shubman Gill dismissed Pat Cummins' claims about the effectiveness of Australia's short-ball tactic in Adelaide.  Cummins suggested they might use it again in the third Test, but Gill pointed out it mainly dismissed lower-order batsmen.  Gill, confident in India's batting, aims for a substantial first-innings total after their previous low scores.
title: Shubman Gill hands Pat Cummins a reality check
RG Kar case: Former principal Sandip Ghosh gets bail

description: The Border-Gavaskar series is level at 1-1 as India and Australia head to The Gabba for a crucial third Test. Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli's form is under scrutiny, mirroring India's first-innings struggles. While Jasprit Bumrah remains India's bowling spearhead, Australia's vulnerability lies in their inconsistent batting, despite Travis Head's explosive potential.
title: WTC scenarios: How 3rd Test could change table

description: Tensions flared in Kadapa district, Andhra Pradesh, during local water society elections.  YSRCP MP YS Avinash Reddy was arrested amidst clashes between YSRCP and TDP supporters at the Vemula MRO office.  Reddy accused the TDP of pressuring officials to block YSRCP candidates.  The ensuing commotion resulted in the injury of several journalists.
title: YSRCP MP YS Avinash Reddy arrested amid tensions over local water society elections

description: Business magnate Anand Mahindra and countless others celebrated 18-year-old Indian chess prodigy D Gukesh's triumph over World Chess Champion Ding Liren.  Gukesh achieved this historic victory in Singapore on December 12th during the World Chess Championship. Mahindra shared a video of Gukesh dancing, reflecting the nation's shared pride and joy.
title: Anand Mahindra shares D Gukesh's Manasilayo dance from Ranjni Kanth movie

description: The Indian cricket team's Test cricket form has plummeted after a strong start to 2024. Four losses in their last five matches, including a 0-3 whitewash against New Zealand, have raised concerns. Inconsistent batting, particularly from senior players, and a struggling bowling attack are the primary reasons for their decline.
title: In numbers: Analysing Team India's downfall in last five Tests

description: Sandalwood actor Darshan Toogudeep Srinivas and six others have been granted bail by the Karnataka High Court in the Renukaswamy murder case. Renukaswamy was allegedly kidnapped, tortured, and murdered in Bengaluru on June 8.
title: Renukaswamy case: Karnataka HC grants regular bail to actor Darshan

description: Greg Chappell compares Jasprit Bumrah to legendary fast bowlers like Andy Roberts and Dennis Lillee, highlighting Bumrah's unique blend of skill, strategy, and control. Chappell argues that Bumrah's exceptional performance poses the biggest challenge to Australia's hopes of winning the Border-Gavaskar Trophy.
title: 'Bumrah combination of legendary pacers...': Chappell hails seamer

description: A Madhya Pradesh businessman and his wife were found dead in an apparent suicide after facing investigation by the Enforcement Directorate (ED). The couple was reportedly under stress due to the probe linked to a 2017 fraud case.
title: Couple whose kids gifted Rahul Gandhi their piggy bank found hanging at home
'It's Samvidhan, not sangh ka vidhan': Priyanka in maiden LS speech

description: Thyssenkrupp Marine Systems (TKMS) aims to establish India as a global submarine and warship construction hub, citing potential 50% cost reductions.  Competing for a major Indian Navy contract, TKMS proposes a collaborative center with Mazagaon Dockyards Limited, eyeing future export opportunities amid rising global demand.
title: Germany’s Thyssenkrupp eyes P75I contract to make submarines in India

description: Bengaluru tech professional Atul Subhash was found dead, leaving behind a video and note accusing his wife, Nikita Singhania, of harassment and extortion.  Outrage on social media led Accenture CEO Julie Sweet to lock her X profile.
title: After Nikita Singhania, Accenture locks Julie Sweet's Twitter handle

description: Russia unleashed a massive missile and drone attack on Ukraine's energy infrastructure, firing 93 missiles, including one reportedly from North Korea, and nearly 200 drones.  Ukraine's air defenses, including newly acquired F-16s, intercepted a significant portion of the missiles. President Zelenskyy condemned the attack and appealed for stronger international sanctions and increased air defense support.
title: Russia fires 93 missiles at Ukraine in massive strike: Zelenskyy

description: Shubman Gill, back at the Gabba where he shone in India's 2021 series win, exudes confidence ahead of the third Test. The series is tied 1-1, and India aims for a big first-innings total with the red ball after two sub-par batting performances in Adelaide. Captain Rohit Sharma, returning after missing the first Test, skipped Friday's optional training.
title: 'I think Rohit Sharma has practised enough,': Shubman Gill

description: Jeff Bezos remains deeply engaged in Amazon's AI strategy, dedicating significant time to its development, according to Rohit Prasad, Amazon's AI head.  Prasad dismissed concerns about AI development slowing down, highlighting continuous breakthroughs.  Amazon recently unveiled its Nova family of LLMs, aiming to compete with major AI players, and is also revamping Alexa for more natural interactions and enhanced capabilities.
title: Amazon AI head on Jeff Bezos being back at the company: Very fortunate for…

description: Indian pacer Navdeep Saini recounts the historic Gabba Test victory in 2021, revealing his battle with a groin injury throughout the match. Despite the pain, Saini pushed through, fueled by painkillers and team spirit. He describes the dropped catch, the unexpected call to bat in the final moments, and the adrenaline rush that masked his injury as he ran.
title: Exclusive | The unheard story from India's Gabba glory

description: Nearly 18,000 undocumented Indians in the US face deportation as the Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) prepares a list ahead of President-elect Trump's term. ICE data reveals thousands of Indians await legal status, with hearings scheduled years later. The US government has labeled India "uncooperative" due to delays in accepting deportees, adding to the complexity.
title: 18k Indians in deportation line as Trump vows tough action

description: India and Australia are locked in a crucial third Test at the Gabba, with the series tied 1-1. Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli's form is under scrutiny, while Jasprit Bumrah has been India's standout bowler. Australia's batting vulnerabilities offer India a chance, but the hosts are wary of their reliance on Bumrah.
title: Eyes on Virat and Rohit as India gear up for make-or-break Gabba Test

description: India's Test series against Australia is poised at 1-1, with concerns surrounding India's batting inconsistencies and support for Jasprit Bumrah in the attack.  Former selector Sunil Joshi suggests Rohit Sharma should open, emphasizes the need for strong character in the batting lineup, and recommends Ashwin's experience for the Gabba Test.
title: 'Show strong character': Ex-chief selector's message to India batters

description: Kolkata police are investigating a gruesome discovery. A severed head, likely female, was found in a plastic bag at a Tollygunge waste site. Authorities rushed to the scene on Friday morning. The head was sent to M R Bangur Hospital. Police are searching for the remaining body parts. A local councillor alerted authorities after residents reported the grim find.
title: Severed human head found in garbage dump in Kolkata's Tollygunge

description: Actor Allu Arjun was arrested in Hyderabad after a deadly stampede at the premiere of his film "Pushpa 2: The Rule."  The incident killed one and critically injured another.  Arjun is facing charges related to culpable homicide and negligence due to inadequate crowd control. He offered condolences and financial support to the victim's family.
title: Allu Arjun seen smiling, drinking coffee during arrest

description: A viral TikTok video by a pilot explains the importance of airplane mode. He describes how multiple phones seeking cell signals can interfere with pilots' headsets, creating a distracting buzzing sound. This interference can hinder communication with air traffic control, potentially impacting flight safety.
title: Pilot explains the 'big reason' phones need to be in Airplane Mode

description: Uproar in Rajya Sabha as opposition parties moved a no-confidence motion against Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar, citing partisan conduct.  Heated exchanges ensued, with Dhankhar and Congress President Kharge clashing over speaking time and alleged insults.  The Rajya Sabha adjourned until December 16 after failing to resolve the impasse.
title: 'I have tolerated a lot': Dhankhar vs Kharge faceoff in Rajya Sabha; see video
Actor Allu Arjun arrested in Sandhya Theatre stampede case

description: The third Australia-India Test at the Gabba faces potential rain disruptions throughout the first four days, impacting the decisive match.  The Gabba pitch, known for pace and bounce, will test batting skills, while overcast conditions may favour swing bowlers.  Both teams will be racing against time and weather to secure a result in this crucial encounter.
title: Brisbane Weather Report: Will rain impact IND vs AUS 3rd Test?

description: Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2" continues its box office reign, nearing the highest-grossing film of 2024 title.  Earning ₹726.25 crore in its first week, the sequel surpasses major hits like "Jawan" and "Kalki."  Day 9 saw another ₹1.21 crore, bringing the total to ₹727.46 crore, proving it lives up to the hype generated by the first installment.
title: Allu Arjun and Rashmika Mandanna starrer ‘Pushpa 2’ mints 1.21 Cr net in India

description: Connor Gaydos, the new CEO of the relaunched Enron, known for the "Birds Aren't Real" theory, was recently pied in the face.  The incident, captured on video, has gone viral, drawing comparisons to Bill Gates' similar experience. Gaydos' company acquired the Enron name in 2020, aiming for a revolutionary comeback after the company's infamous collapse.
title: Remake of Bill Gates incident? Connor Gaydos hit with 'pie in face'- Watch

description: Blinkit has launched Bistro, a standalone app offering 10-minute food delivery, competing with Zepto Cafe and Swiggy Bolt. Leveraging its existing network, Bistro aims to provide quick snacks, meals, and beverages. This marks Zomato's second attempt in the 10-minute delivery space after the discontinuation of Zomato Instant.
title: Blinkit launches Bistro app: To offer 10-minute food delivery and more

description: Akasa Air is securing a substantial minority stake investment of $130-140 million from a consortium led by Premji Invest and Claypond Capital.
title: Azim Premji-Ranjan Pai family offices to buy stake in Akasa Air

description: The Unique Identification Authority of India (UIDAI) allows Aadhaar cardholders to update their information online for free until December 14, 2024, via the myAadhaar portal.
title: Deadline for free Aadhar Card update ends on December 14- how to update it online

description: Shubman Gill reminisced about India's 2021 Gabba victory as the team prepares for the crucial third Test against Australia.  He acknowledged the challenges of the pink ball and night conditions in Adelaide, emphasizing the importance of mental fortitude.  Confident in India's ability, Gill dismissed any fear, focusing on the current ball rather than the bowler, echoing the team's fearless approach.
title: This generation doesn't think about who's bowling: Shubman Gill

description: D Gukesh, an 18-year-old Indian chess prodigy, became the youngest World Chess Champion after defeating Ding Liren.  A heartwarming video capturing his father's emotional reaction to the victory went viral, showcasing the family's joy and pride. Gukesh's achievement highlights India's rising prominence in the world of chess. Read the article to know more.
title: Gukesh's dad's heartwarming reaction to son's World Chess Championship win

description: A 55-year-old woman, Kaneez Fatima Ansari, tragically died in a Kurla bus accident on Monday.  A disturbing video shows a helmeted man stealing her gold bangles and purse as she lay lifeless under a car. Police have registered a theft case and are working to identify the suspect. Ansari's daughter expressed outrage at this inhumane act.
title: Mumbai bus crash: Video shows man stealing bangles from victim’s hand

description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi criticized PM Modi's meeting with the Kapoor family, urging him to focus on "real issues". Gandhi contrasted his interactions with workers to Modi's engagement with film stars. This follows criticism from Congress MP Manickam Tagore, who pointed out the government's seemingly different reactions to Modi and Gandhi's meetings with different groups.
title: 'Cut, cut, cut': Rahul takes a jibe at PM over meeting with Kapoor family

description: Winter's harsh conditions can severely dry your skin.  Natural oils, like argan, rosehip, squalane, marula, and jojoba, offer a potent solution. These oils replenish lost moisture, acting as a protective shield against the elements.  Applying them on damp skin after showering or mixing them with moisturizer maximizes their hydrating benefits for a healthy winter glow.
title: Prepare your skin for the winter: Discover the best oils to use

description: Luigi Mangione, suspected of killing UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson, traveled through Asia before vanishing.  He resurfaced in New York City after being reported missing and allegedly committed the murder.  Investigators are probing his travels, a past back injury, and social media posts expressing anger towards insurance companies.
title: Luigi Mangione went on Asia trip for months before allegedly killing CEO

description: Elon Musk plans to establish Starbase, its South Texas launch site, as an incorporated city.  The company sent a letter to Cameron county officials requesting an election for incorporation, citing the need to accommodate its growing workforce.  This follows Musk's 2021 proposal for the city and comes amid ongoing legal challenges regarding environmental concerns.
title: 'Designed to alter humanity: Musk wants to transform SpaceX's Starbase to Texas

description: Former Infosys CFO Mohandas Pai criticized the Devanahalli toll plaza near Bengaluru airport, questioning its high charges and unique placement on the main airport route.  He highlighted the plaza's ₹308 crore revenue in 2023-24 and urged its removal, suggesting relocation further down Bellary Road. Pai emphasized no other Indian airport has a toll on its primary access road.
title: Ex Infosys CFO to Nitin Gadkari: Why this discrimination against B'luru?

description: Around 400 IndiGo passengers were stranded at Istanbul Airport for over 24 hours due to flight delays and cancellations. Passengers reported a lack of communication, accommodation, and meal vouchers from the airline. They faced difficulties due to the chilly weather and limited lounge access.
title: 'No accommodation, food': Over 400 IndiGo flyers stuck in Istanbul for over a day

description: Political tensions rise as Assam's Chief Minister questions Mamata Banerjee's interest in leading the opposition alliance.  Banerjee receives support from various leaders, including Lalu Prasad and Sharad Pawar.  However, the Congress and BJP's parliamentary actions draw criticism from other parties.  TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee expresses concern over the dominance of the two major parties in parliamentary proceedings.
title: As whispers grow louder for Didi's INDIA leadership, Himanta's 'dead' alliance warning

description: A 31-year-old man from Mumbra, Thane, has been charged for allegedly divorcing his 25-year-old wife by 'triple talaq' on Tuesday. He reportedly contacted his wife's father to declare the divorce, citing her independent walks as the reason.
title: Man gives 'triple talaq' to wife for going alone for walk

description: Mumbai police are investigating a bomb threat against the Reserve Bank of India.  An email written in Russian, threatening to detonate explosives, was received through the bank's official website.  A case has been filed at the MRA Marg police station against an unidentified individual.  Authorities are actively working to determine the source and credibility of the threat.
title: RBI receives bomb threat in Russian language, second in a month

description: D Gukesh clinched the World Chess Championship title on Thursday, defeating Ding Liren. Russian Chess Federation President Andrei Filatov has controversially accused Ding of intentionally losing and demanded an investigation by FIDE. Gukesh is the first Indian champion since his mentor Viswanathan Anand.
title: Russian Chess chief accuses Liren of losing on purpose

description: Police arrested Luigi Mangione, 26, in Pennsylvania for the murder of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson in NYC.  Mangione's July back injury and subsequent surgery are suspected motives.  A note criticizing the US healthcare system and a notebook detailing the murder plan were found with Mangione. He is fighting extradition to New York.
title: What drove suspect to kill UnitedHealthcare CEO? Cops share new details

description: The White House has launched a national strategy to combat Islamophobia, outlining over 100 measures to address hate and discrimination against Muslims and Arab Americans. This initiative, modeled after a similar plan to combat antisemitism, comes amid rising concerns about such bigotry, exemplified by the tragic murder of a 6-year-old Muslim boy.
title: Biden admin unveils historic national strategy to combat Islamophobia

description: Mysterious drones have been buzzing over New Jersey, sparking UFO theories and concerns. The Pentagon denies any foreign involvement, specifically dismissing Rep. Jeff Van Drew's suggestion of an Iranian "mothership." However, the FBI admits uncertainty, even suggesting some sightings might be misidentified aircraft.
title: No evidence to suggest New Jersey drones work of foreign adversary: WH

description: Chennai's Chembarambakkam Lake is nearing full capacity due to heavy rainfall, prompting authorities to release 1,000 cusecs of water starting Friday morning. A flood warning has been issued for nearby areas, including villages along the Adyar River. With inflow exceeding 6,000 cusecs and expected to rise, officials warn the release volume will likely increase to prevent widespread flooding.
title: Chennai flood warning: 1,000 cusecs of water to be released from Chembarambakkam Lake

description: NASA's Juno mission revealed that Jupiter's moon, Io, the most volcanic body in our solar system, doesn't possess a global magma ocean.  Instead, separate magma chambers fuel its over 400 active volcanoes, solving a 44-year-old mystery.  Juno's gravity data, collected during recent flybys, confirms this, impacting our understanding of other moons and exoplanets.
title: 'Heart of Jupiter moon Io's rage': Nasa captures active volcano erupting into space
Buy or sell: Stocks on brokerages’ radar for today

description: Travis Timmerman, a US citizen, has been freed after months of detention in a Syrian prison following the Assad regime's overthrow. He was found on Thursday and recounted his experience to CBS News, detailing his unauthorized entry into Syria and subsequent capture.  Timmerman is now seeking to leave Syria, and the US government is working to bring him home.
title: Who is Travis Timmerman? US man found in Syria after spending months in prison

description: Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2" is shattering box office records, surpassing Hindi-dubbed giants like "KGF 2" in just eight days with a ₹435.5 crore collection.  It's now on track to potentially outgross "Baahubali 2"'s Hindi earnings, setting a new benchmark for South Indian cinema's Hindi market dominance.
title: Pushpa 2 box office: Allu Arjun starrer makes 113% more than ‘KGF 2'

description: Josh Hazlewood returns to Australia's playing eleven for the crucial third Test against India at the Gabba, replacing Scott Boland. Hazlewood recovered fully from a side strain, proving his fitness in recent bowling sessions. Captain Pat Cummins expressed confidence in Hazlewood's recovery and acknowledged Boland's unfortunate omission despite strong performances.
title: Cummins names Australia's playing XI for Gabba Test against India

description: Virat Kohli, despite a recent century, is intensely focused on refining his technique at the Gabba nets, leading India's batting unit in preparation for the crucial third Test. He's working tirelessly, addressing perceived flaws and motivating younger players.
title: 3rd Test: Can Virat Kohli inspire a turnaround at Gabba?

description: Bengaluru police are searching for the Singhania family, accused of abetting the suicide of AI executive Atul Subhash. Subhash, embroiled in a legal battle with his estranged wife Nikita and her family, took his life after allegedly facing demands of Rs 3.3 crore. The family fled their Jaunpur home, prompting a police manhunt.
title: 'Left on bike': Unable to find techie's in-laws, cops paste notice at their house

description: Several Delhi schools, including Bhatnagar International, Cambridge, and DPS Amar Colony, received bomb threats Friday morning, suspending classes.  Fire services responded to calls starting at 4:21 a.m., dispatching tenders to ensure student and staff safety.  Additional calls continued to be received as officials investigated the threats.
title: Multiple schools in Delhi get bomb threat, 2nd in a week

description: A Delhi court acquitted six individuals, including a former coal secretary and company executives, in a coal scam case. The court found no evidence of cheating or misrepresentation by Navbharat Power Pvt Ltd (later Brahmani Thermal Power) in obtaining Odisha coal blocks.
title: Court acquits ex-coal secy, 4 others & firm in Odisha coal scam case

description: In a heartwarming display of unity, villagers in Assam's Jorhat district rescued four wild elephants, including a struggling calf, trapped in a pond. Hearing the elephants' distressed cries, the villagers quickly mobilized, using tools to carve a makeshift escape route.
title: Village answers trunk calls, saves jumbos

description: The Chandigarh Commission for Protection of Child Rights issued an advisory to singer-actor Diljit Dosanjh, restricting songs mentioning alcohol, drugs, or violence at his upcoming concert.  This follows a similar notice in Telangana.  The commission warned of penal action for non-compliance, citing potential harm to children.  A complaint alleges Dosanjh used altered lyrics in previous performances despite similar restrictions.
title: After Hyd, Chandigarh: Dosanjh asked to keep alcohol, drugs off playlist

description: Former India cricketer Vinod Kambli, 52, reveals his recent health scare involving a severe urine infection and subsequent collapse. Supported by his family, he's now recovering and plans to enter rehab. He also addressed his past grievances with childhood friend Sachin Tendulkar, clarifying that Tendulkar had assisted him financially with surgeries.
title: 'Ready to go to rehab. Sachin did everything for me': Vinod Kambli

description: India bolsters its defence capabilities with a Rs 21,100 crore investment in 100 K-9 Vajra artillery guns and 12 Sukhoi-30MKI fighter jets.  This procurement addresses the need for enhanced firepower in high-altitude regions and replaces aging aircraft, contributing to a stronger national security posture.
title: CCS clears two big-ticket arms deals worth Rs 21,100 crore

description: Emami's MD, Harsha Vardhan Agarwal, new Ficci president, states that consumption slowdown, impacted by inflation, will take a few quarters to normalize.  He suggests controlling inflation and boosting government spending to revive demand, noting a mixed bag for FMCG with rural uptick and urban slowdown.
title: 'Consumption to go up after inflation eases'

description: At its re:Invent conference, Amazon Web Services (AWS) launched new AI models and chips, including the Trainium2 and Nova, to compete with rivals like Microsoft and Google. CEO Andy Jassy emphasized AWS's customer-centric approach to AI, aiming to solve practical problems rather than chasing technological feats.
title: Catch-up: Amazon goes all in on AI

description: Nandan Nilekani reiterated his stance against India investing in building another large language model (LLM). He argues that resources should be directed towards compute, infrastructure, and AI cloud instead.  This contrasts with Google Research India director Manish Gupta's view, who believes India should build its own foundation model, citing Nilekani's Aadhaar project as a precedent.
title: India shouldn't build another LLM: Nandan Nilekani

description: The Supreme Court halted legal battles over temple reclamation claims, freezing existing and barring new 'mosque-temple' lawsuits. This includes the Gyanvapi and Mathura disputes. The order stems from challenges to the 1991 Places of Worship Act, which fixed religious sites' status as of Independence Day 1947, excluding the Ayodhya case.
title: SC: Trial courts not to pass orders on religious places

description: Indore, renowned as India's cleanest city, faces a growing air pollution challenge. A 21% surge in PM10 levels since 2017-18 puts it among India's 'non-attainment' cities. Rapid urbanization, industrial growth, and heavy traffic contribute to worsening air quality, with road dust and vehicle emissions identified as primary culprits.
title: What Swachh ranking won't tell you about Indore's air quality

description: Jason Gillespie has resigned as Pakistan's Test cricket coach due to disagreements with the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB), particularly over the non-renewal of his assistant's contract. Aaqib Javed will replace Gillespie as interim coach for the upcoming South Africa tour. Gillespie's departure follows a pattern of coaching instability within the PCB, raising concerns about their management approach.
title: 'Frustrated' Jason Gillespie resigns as Pakistan Test coach

description: Telecom operators and tech companies are clashing over spam regulations in India.  Telcos want stricter oversight of OTT platforms, arguing they contribute significantly to spam but avoid accountability. Tech companies counter that existing laws suffice.  TRAI is reviewing the regulations and aims to create a balanced approach.
title: WhatsApp, Google to Airtel, Jio: Your views are misplaced...

description: WhatsApp has rolled out new calling features for desktop and mobile to enhance user experience.  These include selecting specific participants in group calls, adding fun effects to video calls, improved call access on the desktop app, and enhanced video quality for clearer conversations.
title: WhatsApp rolls out new features: Select participants in Group calls and...

description: In Hyderabad's Bharat Nagar, a couple was discovered hoarding hundreds of stolen shoes and slippers in their home.  A neighbor's suspicion led to the discovery of the footwear fortress, where residents identified their missing belongings.  The couple, caught on CCTV, had been selling the stolen footwear throughout the city. Police registered a theft case against them.
title: Footwear heist: Hyderabad couple held with over 100 stolen pairs
